Kanji Keywords: Heisig 6th Edition vs. jpdb.io

This comparison table shows the kanji keywords for Heisig's Remembering the Kanji, 6th Edition and jpdb.io.

Keyword collisions are indicated in parentheses. Note that some jpdb keywords collide not just with Heisig's keywords but also with other jpdb keywords. For example, 晶 and 璃 are both named "crystal". Also note that collision detection is not perfect. We use the stem of the keyword for comparison to catch as many possible collisions as possible.

You can also download this table as a CSV file.
